Both required outputs are in place in the bundle directory:

- `transcript.json` (48 KB) — 25 iterations, schema-validated, with `dataset_id=ds001_crc`, `model_id=claude-opus-4-7`, `harness_id=claude-code-custom@v1`, `max_iterations=25`. Each iteration carries self-contained hypotheses naming the actual columns and signed direction, plus analyses with `hypothesis_ids`, `effect_estimate`, `p_value`, and `significant`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` (13 KB) — narrative covering main effects, multivariable structure (R²=0.86), interaction/subgroup probes, equity analysis, and split-half replication.

Headline findings: `feature_078` (rho=+0.785), `feature_051` (-1.35 mo), `feature_038` (+0.97 mo), and `feature_057` (-1.18 mo per level) dominate. Treatment-like benefit of `feature_038` is uniform across race, insurance, and clinical strata; the only meaningful effect modifier was `feature_092` (interaction p=4.1e-5) in the adjusted multivariable model. Race and insurance show no independent or mediated PFS effects in this cohort.
